docs.abstract: At no point have black trans people shared fully in the gains of the L.G.B.T.Q. or racial justice movements. This may be changing.
docs.snippet: At no point have black trans people shared fully in the gains of the L.G.B.T.Q. or racial justice movements. This may be changing.
docs.lead_paragraph: Transgender women of color were leaders in L.G.B.T.Q. activism before, during and after the uprising at the Stonewall Inn 51 years ago on Sunday, but they were never put at the center of the movement they helped start: one whose very shorthand, “the gay rights movement,” erases them.

headline.main: Black Trans Women Seek More Space in the Movement They Helped Start

byline.original: By Isabella Grullón Paz and Maggie Astor

docs.abstract: The invisibility of Drake’s Cross in a San Francisco park may make it the most fitting monument to white supremacy in the country.
docs.snippet: The invisibility of Drake’s Cross in a San Francisco park may make it the most fitting monument to white supremacy in the country.
docs.lead_paragraph: Monuments are symbols, and in times of trouble they prompt symbolic action. They went up as political statements, and they come down as political statements. But it is far easier to topple a monument or change a name than to eradicate racism or counter its long legacy.

headline.main: This Monument to White Supremacy Hides in Plain Sight

docs.abstract: Amid widespread protests over police brutality after the death of George Floyd, some federal and local officials have blamed outsiders for stoking violence. Similar claims were made during the civil rights movement.
docs.snippet: Amid widespread protests over police brutality after the death of George Floyd, some federal and local officials have blamed outsiders for stoking violence. Similar claims were made during the civil rights movement.
docs.lead_paragraph: After demonstrations for racial equality in Alabama were inflamed by the killing of Jimmie Lee Jackson, 26, a black activist who was shot by a state trooper, state officials issued a resolution asking people to stay home, citing “continued agitation and demonstrations led and directed by outsiders.”

headline.main: The Long History of the ‘Outside Agitator’

docs.abstract: Streaming services have pulled a host of British comedy series featuring blackface. The actions highlight the fact that racist depictions weren’t just a thing of the past.
docs.snippet: Streaming services have pulled a host of British comedy series featuring blackface. The actions highlight the fact that racist depictions weren’t just a thing of the past.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — On Thursday night, the British chat-show host Trisha Goddard discussed the impact of an impersonation of her by a white comedian in blackface that was popular on television here in the early 2000s.

headline.main: Blackface on British TV Finally Faces a Reckoning
